## Additional Context
T1.3: Two tasks — create configs/smoke_sft_local.yaml and add --local flag to scripts/hpc/preflight.sh.

Task A — Create configs/smoke_sft_local.yaml:
Read configs/smoke_sft.yaml first to understand the extends: format.
Create configs/smoke_sft_local.yaml with:
```yaml
# LOCAL SMOKE ONLY — NOT FOR SUBMISSION. Validates pipeline plumbing; uses non-frozen base model.
extends: configs/smoke_sft.yaml
base_model: Qwen/Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct
lora_r: 8
lora_alpha: 16
target_modules:
  - q_proj
  - k_proj
  - v_proj
  - o_proj
dataset_max_rows: 100
max_steps: 20
save_steps: 10
```

Task B — Edit scripts/hpc/preflight.sh to add --local flag:
Read the current preflight.sh to understand its structure.
Add a --local flag (parse from $@ using getopts or a simple loop).
When --local is passed:
  - Skip the BASE_MODEL_ID equality check (frozen model ID check)
  - Skip the model weights path check (model pre-staged check)
  - Still run: CUDA availability, disk space, package importability, dataset SHA256 checks
Default behavior (no --local) must be completely unchanged.

Commit both: git add configs/smoke_sft_local.yaml scripts/hpc/preflight.sh && git commit -m 'feat(hpc): add smoke_sft_local.yaml and preflight --local flag'

Begin implementing the feature now.